### OpenSSL documentation policy

- Follow OpenSSL docs policy for new/changed APIs and options: British English, POD manpages in `doc/man*`, CHANGES/NEWS notes, and `make doc-nits` before PRs.
- References:
  - Policy: `https://www.openssl.org/policies/technical/documentation-policy.html`
  - HOWTO: `doc/HOWTO/documenting-functions-and-macros.md`

### Required developer actions

- For new commands/args: add POD in `doc/man1/`.
- For new public symbols: add POD in `doc/man3/` and update `util/lib{crypto,ssl}.num` via `make update`.
- For overviews/conventions: add POD in `doc/man7/`.
- For configure options: update `INSTALL.md`.
- Run and fix: `make doc-nits` and `make md-nits`.

### Markdown hygiene (mdformat/markdownlint)

- Enforce common rules: MD001, MD003, MD009, MD022, MD031, MD032, MD034, MD036, MD040, MD047, MD055, MD057.
- Use `scripts/format_markdown.sh` for auto-fix, or `--check` in CI.

### CI integration

- In check-docs workflows: run `./config && make -s build_generated && make doc-nits`, then `scripts/format_markdown.sh --check`.
- In commit style checks: verify Markdown formatting when `.md` files change.

